WEBVTT

00:00:04.630 --> 00:00:09.802
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.761 --> 00:00:13.764
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:16.767
At least it is true...

00:00:17.143 --> 00:00:20.730
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:24.775 --> 00:00:25.776
H-Hey!

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:33.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

00:00:35.703 --> 00:00:36.454
Guts!

00:01:03.856 --> 00:01:05.816
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:06.025 --> 00:01:07.818
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:07.943 --> 00:01:11.530
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:11.697 --> 00:01:13.908
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:14.033 --> 00:01:15.951
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:16.077 --> 00:01:18.204
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:18.329 --> 00:01:20.039
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:20.206 --> 00:01:23.667
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:24.335 --> 00:01:27.338
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:28.089 --> 00:01:28.714
<i>I...</i>

00:01:29.090 --> 00:01:29.799
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:29.924 --> 00:01:31.967
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:01:32.093 --> 00:01:32.968
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:33.219 --> 00:01:33.969
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:34.095 --> 00:01:35.805
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:01:35.971 --> 00:01:36.972
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:37.181 --> 00:01:37.932
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:38.099 --> 00:01:39.850
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:01:40.101 --> 00:01:41.102
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:41.227 --> 00:01:42.061
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:01:42.228 --> 00:01:43.687
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:01:43.979 --> 00:01:44.980
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:45.231 --> 00:01:46.107
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:01:46.232 --> 00:01:46.941
<i>Too late...</i>

00:01:47.066 --> 00:01:48.567
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:01:53.614 --> 00:01:57.618
Together

00:01:58.994 --> 00:02:01.580
It's up to you whether
you want to follow me or not.

00:02:04.208 --> 00:02:06.710
Now you've learned what it
means to fight, haven't you?

00:02:28.315 --> 00:02:29.066
Hey.

00:02:39.451 --> 00:02:40.578
Where am I?

00:02:40.953 --> 00:02:42.705
You are in a cave by the river.

00:02:43.038 --> 00:02:45.082
Luckily, we fell into
the river and survived.

00:02:46.083 --> 00:02:47.042
A river?

00:02:47.710 --> 00:02:50.421
Come on, don't you
remember anything?

00:02:51.088 --> 00:02:54.592
We were about to die from drowning,
but you don't seem too worried about that!

00:02:57.720 --> 00:02:58.304
Dammit!

00:02:58.470 --> 00:03:00.973
Don't get up yet, your fever
hasn't completely gone down.

00:03:05.477 --> 00:03:09.565
You can't blame me, you were
freezing and completely drenched.

00:03:14.195 --> 00:03:15.613
What are you looking at?

00:03:17.615 --> 00:03:19.366
That hurt, what's the meaning of this?

00:03:19.742 --> 00:03:21.619
I'm the one who saved your life!

00:03:21.869 --> 00:03:22.828
Shit, stop it!

00:03:25.372 --> 00:03:26.498
Oh, lay off!

00:03:35.841 --> 00:03:37.635
Enough of this crap!

00:03:37.760 --> 00:03:39.261
You're hysterical!

00:03:40.262 --> 00:03:42.389
I didn't mean to go out
of my way for you, but...

00:03:42.514 --> 00:03:45.851
Even though you were covered in armor,
I desperately dragged you from the river!

00:03:46.393 --> 00:03:48.020
After that, you haven't thanked me.

00:03:48.145 --> 00:03:49.521
How dare you throw a knife at me?

00:03:49.897 --> 00:03:53.525
I'd beat you and dislocate
your jaw if you weren't a woman!

00:03:55.861 --> 00:04:00.032
I do not like it, a mere woman
such as you, acting like a knight.

00:04:00.991 --> 00:04:03.911
You're easily driven into a frenzy.

00:04:04.662 --> 00:04:07.289
That's why a woman
like you isn't cut out for war.

00:04:10.417 --> 00:04:10.876
Hey...

00:04:15.172 --> 00:04:16.507
Not my choice...

00:04:18.008 --> 00:04:19.218
I was not...

00:04:21.262 --> 00:04:23.639
I was not born to
be a woman by choice!

00:04:26.600 --> 00:04:28.227
Well, I'm sorry.

00:04:30.896 --> 00:04:31.647
Damn you!

00:04:31.772 --> 00:04:33.274
You crazy broad!

00:04:33.524 --> 00:04:34.900
Why don't you try to calm down?

00:04:35.150 --> 00:04:36.235
Hands off!

00:04:37.611 --> 00:04:38.404
Let go...

00:04:38.779 --> 00:04:39.738
...of me...

00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:48.289
I told you so.

00:04:51.542 --> 00:04:53.252
Hey, put this on.

00:04:54.044 --> 00:04:56.046
It dried out while I was wearing it.

00:04:58.674 --> 00:04:59.800
What?

00:05:00.009 --> 00:05:01.135
Are you still crying?

00:05:01.552 --> 00:05:02.261
Shut up!

00:05:02.303 --> 00:05:03.178
Turn around now!

00:05:05.180 --> 00:05:06.807
How pathetic...

00:05:07.057 --> 00:05:09.935
Whatever happened to me,
I would have never asked for your help.

00:05:11.061 --> 00:05:13.314
Great, she really hates me.

00:05:15.065 --> 00:05:18.527
Hey, why did you enlist in
the Band of the Hawk anyway?

00:05:19.069 --> 00:05:21.071
Isn't it tough to be a
woman in this business?

00:05:21.572 --> 00:05:22.948
No matter the circumstances...

00:05:25.200 --> 00:05:27.828
Well, it's not my business, I guess.

00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:30.914
Griffith...

00:05:35.544 --> 00:05:36.795
It's because of Griffith.

00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:46.096
I'm from a small farming
village deep in the mountains.

00:05:47.973 --> 00:05:51.435
The crops were meager
and the soil was sterile...

00:05:52.728 --> 00:05:58.067
Nevertheless, we had been bled
dry by heavy taxes for the war effort.

00:05:59.443 --> 00:06:02.863
Frequently, we would eat
nothing for three days at a time.

00:06:06.075 --> 00:06:08.118
Many people died
of hunger each winter...

00:06:08.619 --> 00:06:13.248
Our village was along the border, so
it often became involved in skirmishes.

00:06:14.833 --> 00:06:16.502
Each time it happened...

00:06:16.752 --> 00:06:21.006
We were forced to watch them trample
our houses and fields, unable to protest.

00:06:22.216 --> 00:06:24.259
There were similar stories
from all the nearby villages.

00:06:25.386 --> 00:06:29.139
Everyone was used to being plundered
and having their lives crushed...

00:06:29.765 --> 00:06:33.602
And I thought it was
just a matter of course.

00:06:35.604 --> 00:06:37.022
One day...

00:06:42.778 --> 00:06:44.488
A nobleman was passing by our village...

00:06:45.489 --> 00:06:47.157
...and I caught his eye.

00:06:48.409 --> 00:06:52.496
The nobleman offered to
take me as his waiting maid.

00:06:53.539 --> 00:06:57.126
After hesitating for a while,
my father ended up accepting his offer.

00:06:59.128 --> 00:07:01.922
I took it for granted that my father
would give the noble his youngest daughter...

00:07:02.047 --> 00:07:04.174
...who was not of
much help to the family.

00:07:04.550 --> 00:07:06.552
My parents had to reduce
the number of mouths to feed.

00:07:07.511 --> 00:07:08.303
However...

00:07:27.823 --> 00:07:29.700
It's no wonder that it
turned out the way it did...

00:07:30.576 --> 00:07:31.452
It couldn't be true...

00:07:31.577 --> 00:07:33.328
...that a noble would take the trouble...

00:07:33.454 --> 00:07:36.832
...to save a girl from a poor family
out of kindness, that would be whimsy.

00:07:47.968 --> 00:07:49.219
There is no choice...

00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:52.222
...this is just how things are...

00:07:52.723 --> 00:07:56.852
Thinking like that always
convinced me to face reality.

00:08:05.736 --> 00:08:09.865
Who do you think you are, does
being nobility make you chosen by God?

00:08:12.117 --> 00:08:15.746
He looked divine and
the moment was unreal.

00:08:16.747 --> 00:08:21.877
God mercifully sent an angel
to this pathetic, powerless girl.

00:08:22.711 --> 00:08:25.255
I really believed that for a moment.

00:08:26.340 --> 00:08:32.012
But, what the angel gave me
was not the helping hand I expected.

00:08:33.805 --> 00:08:37.059
If you have something
to protect, take the sword!

00:09:00.207 --> 00:09:01.667
I was frightened.

00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:06.296
Whether I stabbed
him with the sword...

00:09:07.089 --> 00:09:10.092
...or he accidentally impaled himself...

00:09:11.468 --> 00:09:14.972
Whichever happened, I had killed a man.

00:09:24.064 --> 00:09:27.985
The stranger just
nodded slowly and knowingly.

00:09:29.987 --> 00:09:35.450
It was then I realized that he
had extended to me a true helping hand.

00:09:36.493 --> 00:09:38.829
Griffith, we've cleared everything out.

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:44.251
Hey, wait...

00:09:46.628 --> 00:09:48.714
What am I supposed to do?

00:09:51.842 --> 00:09:53.218
Do whatever you like.

00:09:55.512 --> 00:09:56.513
I want...

00:09:58.515 --> 00:10:00.142
Please bring me with you!

00:10:00.892 --> 00:10:03.353
No way, don't make jokes.

00:10:03.604 --> 00:10:05.981
We are not just petty thieves!

00:10:06.148 --> 00:10:09.526
We are collecting war
funds in order to raise an army!

00:10:09.776 --> 00:10:12.904
It would be a joke if we went off to
war accompanied by kids and women!

00:10:13.363 --> 00:10:16.908
Please, I will learn how to
wield a sword if you demand it!

00:10:17.159 --> 00:10:18.035
So please...

00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:20.621
Oh boy, she's serious.

00:10:21.163 --> 00:10:22.873
What if you wind up dead?

00:10:27.669 --> 00:10:28.754
I told you...

00:10:29.129 --> 00:10:30.547
Do whatever you like.

00:10:30.797 --> 00:10:33.425
It's up to you
whether to follow me or not.

00:10:34.301 --> 00:10:36.678
Now you've learned what it
means to fight, haven't you?

00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:42.434
But...

00:10:44.895 --> 00:10:48.273
It's you who gave me
a sword and a blanket.

00:10:50.150 --> 00:10:53.320
Everything has changed
since the clay I met him.

00:10:54.446 --> 00:10:56.698
My old way of living, where I just
tolerated everything and waited...

00:10:56.823 --> 00:10:58.784
...turned into a new life, where I
would fight to win what I wanted.

00:10:59.660 --> 00:11:03.580
Of course, I worshipped Griffith.

00:11:10.212 --> 00:11:11.213
I think...

00:11:12.214 --> 00:11:15.217
...I'm still lost in a dream.

00:11:16.343 --> 00:11:20.806
An outcast band of commoners has
become an invincible army in battle.

00:11:21.598 --> 00:11:24.226
It's like a miracle
the way we have fought.

00:11:25.936 --> 00:11:31.316
Above everything, our leader is a
young man who still seems so innocent.

00:11:31.483 --> 00:11:35.362
His origin is even
common, just like ours.

00:11:36.238 --> 00:11:37.239
A miracle!

00:11:37.989 --> 00:11:41.702
For me, Griffith
embodied the very idea of a miracle.

00:11:44.705 --> 00:11:48.583
While I managed to make
myself a soldier somehow...

00:11:49.251 --> 00:11:53.630
...the Hawks became involved in a
territorial dispute led by a local nobleman.

00:11:55.090 --> 00:11:59.636
The nobleman was well
known and very wealthy.

00:12:00.512 --> 00:12:04.224
But he had a bad reputation
that didn't reflect his wealth...

00:12:04.391 --> 00:12:06.226
...derived from his unsavory tastes.

00:12:07.394 --> 00:12:11.898
Officially, he hired young
kids from villages as his valets.

00:12:12.524 --> 00:12:16.611
In reality, the kids were imprisoned
to serve the noble's taste for pederasty.

00:12:18.155 --> 00:12:21.992
Their eyes looked
vacant and numbly frightened.

00:12:23.910 --> 00:12:27.038
I felt a chill go down my spine.

00:12:28.039 --> 00:12:31.543
Fear and hatred welled up inside
me, I was totally horrified at the sight.

00:12:32.419 --> 00:12:35.505
It reminded me that a such a
thing could have happened to me.

00:12:39.760 --> 00:12:41.428
It was the same hand that saved me...

00:12:42.554 --> 00:12:44.139
...that he put on my shoulder then.

00:12:44.681 --> 00:12:48.268
Wonderfully, his hand
always stopped my shivering.

00:12:50.562 --> 00:12:52.773
Later, after we had been
through several skirmishes...

00:12:55.066 --> 00:13:00.781
The boy was an apprentice soldier who
had enlisted in the Hawks half a year before.

00:13:01.698 --> 00:13:02.824
Griffith.

00:13:04.534 --> 00:13:05.285
What's that?

00:13:05.452 --> 00:13:07.204
The boy's belongings...

00:13:13.960 --> 00:13:14.961
Griffith?

00:13:15.337 --> 00:13:17.964
He must have really
wanted to be a knight.

00:13:22.344 --> 00:13:24.471
I remember this boy well.

00:13:25.597 --> 00:13:28.350
He always gazed at me as one
might admire the hero of a story.

00:13:28.725 --> 00:13:30.435
I wonder if he was happy.

00:13:33.855 --> 00:13:40.821
Was he able to die as if in a dream,
a dream that was close to being fulfilled?

00:13:42.489 --> 00:13:46.993
I think my dream must
have murdered this boy.

00:13:50.622 --> 00:13:53.959
Before then, I had never
seen Griffith so depressed.

00:13:54.125 --> 00:13:57.212
A man like Griffith
let his shoulders droop.

00:13:57.963 --> 00:14:03.260
And since that moment, Griffith
gradually began to look different.

00:14:04.594 --> 00:14:07.514
It was a few days after we returned
from that battle, and night had fallen.

00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:16.356
Griffith!

00:14:24.406 --> 00:14:26.408
No way, you've got to be kidding!

00:14:26.616 --> 00:14:28.535
A proud guy like him was...

00:14:49.014 --> 00:14:49.764
Caska“.

00:14:50.765 --> 00:14:52.517
It feels so nice, won't you join me?

00:14:53.685 --> 00:14:56.271
Well, I, uh...

00:14:57.397 --> 00:14:59.274
You think I'm disgusting?

00:14:59.524 --> 00:15:00.400
No...

00:15:03.695 --> 00:15:04.654
Why...

00:15:06.656 --> 00:15:08.575
Why were you there last night?

00:15:11.953 --> 00:15:15.457
Wait a minute, I was mistaken, right?

00:15:15.957 --> 00:15:19.169
You were there for a war
council or something last night.

00:15:19.669 --> 00:15:20.211
No...

00:15:20.670 --> 00:15:21.338
What?

00:15:23.840 --> 00:15:25.091
You weren't mistaken.

00:15:27.469 --> 00:15:28.929
How could you, with him?

00:15:30.472 --> 00:15:31.431
For money.

00:15:33.350 --> 00:15:35.852
To maintain an
army costs lots of money.

00:15:36.227 --> 00:15:41.358
Soldiers, horses, equipment,
provisions, nothing is for free.

00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:45.612
But the Band of the Hawk will
grow much larger nevertheless...

00:15:46.237 --> 00:15:47.864
And I must help my army grow.

00:15:48.490 --> 00:15:51.743
That's why I need
such immense war funds.

00:15:53.119 --> 00:15:59.125
And that old man is interested in
me, while I am interested in his fortune.

00:15:59.501 --> 00:16:01.127
Our interests have
come to an agreement.

00:16:01.962 --> 00:16:04.381
No, even so, no way...

00:16:05.006 --> 00:16:06.758
Why can't things stay as they are?

00:16:07.217 --> 00:16:10.762
If we're able to keep on winning, we
could earn all the money you need one day.

00:16:10.971 --> 00:16:13.139
That would take a
tremendous amount of time, and...

00:16:14.599 --> 00:16:18.603
The more we fight in
battles, the more we lose soldiers.

00:16:21.398 --> 00:16:23.900
You mean that boy, don't you?

00:16:24.484 --> 00:16:25.485
No, I don't.

00:16:25.902 --> 00:16:28.279
I came to this conclusion rationally.

00:16:28.905 --> 00:16:33.868
Which brings less risk to me, losing
hundreds of my soldiers in ten battles...

00:16:34.035 --> 00:16:35.870
...or snaring a rich old man?

00:16:36.788 --> 00:16:38.373
Listen, Caska.

00:16:38.790 --> 00:16:44.170
I feel no responsibility to comrades
who've lost their lives due to my commands.

00:16:44.921 --> 00:16:50.385
Because, they chose
to fight in each battle...

00:16:51.511 --> 00:16:52.637
Griffith?

00:16:53.638 --> 00:16:55.557
Just as I chose this...

00:16:58.018 --> 00:17:00.145
But, if there is something that...

00:17:00.937 --> 00:17:02.397
...I can do for them...

00:17:03.314 --> 00:17:05.900
...something I can do for the dead...

00:17:07.360 --> 00:17:08.653
I must fight to win!

00:17:09.279 --> 00:17:13.616
I must keep on winning to attain
my dream, a dream they clung to...

00:17:13.742 --> 00:17:15.035
...and risked their lives for!

00:17:15.618 --> 00:17:16.870
Griffith, stop it!

00:17:17.370 --> 00:17:21.791
I can't just step over the bones
of the dead in order to realize my dream.

00:17:21.916 --> 00:17:23.543
It is a blood-smeared dream, after all.

00:17:24.044 --> 00:17:26.504
I don't regret or feel guilty about it.

00:17:28.256 --> 00:17:33.803
But my dream will never come to
fruition unless I'm willing to get myself dirty.

00:17:34.429 --> 00:17:38.183
And if I don't, then I'll
be risking all those lives...

00:17:41.936 --> 00:17:42.896
Stop it.

00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:44.939
Stop doing it.

00:17:56.409 --> 00:17:57.035
It's all right.

00:17:58.286 --> 00:17:59.454
It's nothing.

00:18:00.705 --> 00:18:05.668
Griffith had already recovered himself
by the time he put his hand on my shoulder.

00:18:06.044 --> 00:18:09.339
And it made me very sad.

00:18:11.174 --> 00:18:13.968
Most people have
abandoned their dreams long ago...

00:18:14.219 --> 00:18:17.347
...but Griffith is still trying to realize his.

00:18:17.847 --> 00:18:20.225
However, he has been forced to...

00:18:20.350 --> 00:18:22.560
...put something immeasurable
on his shoulders, because of...

00:18:22.811 --> 00:18:24.729
...his dream's immensity and purity.

00:18:26.106 --> 00:18:32.112
One who intends to make such a dream
reality inevitably endures terrible things.

00:18:33.363 --> 00:18:34.948
He is not innately strong.

00:18:35.073 --> 00:18:37.742
But now, he has
to be stronger than ever.

00:18:43.123 --> 00:18:46.084
I want to stand by him.

00:18:47.127 --> 00:18:50.463
If he dedicates
himself entirely to his dream...

00:18:51.381 --> 00:18:54.634
If he has to fight to create his dream...

00:18:55.760 --> 00:18:59.347
I want to be a sword for him.

00:19:00.515 --> 00:19:02.142
I want to stand by him.

00:19:02.976 --> 00:19:06.396
I want to be something important,
that will help him fulfill his dream.

00:19:06.896 --> 00:19:09.357
Once, I believed that
my wish would be granted.

00:19:16.281 --> 00:19:18.867
But then came the
time when you appeared before us.

00:19:24.998 --> 00:19:30.003
Do you remember what
Griffith said to you on the hill that day?

00:19:31.254 --> 00:19:33.798
I want you to join us, Guts!

00:19:34.507 --> 00:19:35.675
Those words...

00:19:36.426 --> 00:19:38.803
He had never said
such kind words to anyone.

00:19:41.431 --> 00:19:43.433
I was very annoyed about it.

00:19:44.142 --> 00:19:47.437
I was envious of you,
because Griffith said that about you...

00:19:47.937 --> 00:19:49.147
...as if it were nothing.

00:19:50.064 --> 00:19:53.902
I tried to convince myself...

00:19:54.068 --> 00:19:58.406
...Griffith only needed you as a soldier,
one who would strengthen the Hawks...

00:19:59.949 --> 00:20:05.705
However, a calm man like Griffith acts
impulsively when something happens to you.

00:20:05.955 --> 00:20:06.956
It is as if...

00:20:07.332 --> 00:20:08.208
...as if...

00:20:10.960 --> 00:20:15.048
Griffith has faith in you,
but you don't understand...

00:20:15.590 --> 00:20:17.675
...what the
consequences of that could be!

00:20:21.179 --> 00:20:26.726
I cannot forget the fact that your
selfishness exposed Griffith to lethal danger!

00:20:27.477 --> 00:20:30.355
I don't care if you drop
dead somewhere in battle!

00:20:30.605 --> 00:20:35.944
But, I will never forgive you if
you ruin the Hawks, Griffith's dream!

00:20:37.445 --> 00:20:41.741
And I can't forgive you for
making Griffith change like he has...

00:20:46.871 --> 00:20:47.830
Why?

00:20:49.374 --> 00:20:52.001
Why did he choose you?

00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:53.753
Why you?

00:20:58.091 --> 00:20:59.259
W-What are you doing?

00:20:59.467 --> 00:20:59.968
Shush!

00:21:04.097 --> 00:21:06.975
Hey listen, I think
they're probably dead by now.

00:21:07.141 --> 00:21:08.977
Think about how
they fell from the cliff...

00:21:09.352 --> 00:21:12.522
It doesn't matter
whether they are alive or not.

00:21:12.647 --> 00:21:16.609
Sir Adon promised us
that he will pay the reward...

00:21:17.735 --> 00:21:22.031
Because it's the leader of the Hawk's
Raiders and that female commander.

00:21:22.657 --> 00:21:24.534
Why don't we look
around downstream from here?

00:21:24.784 --> 00:21:27.787
The bodies may have
drifted because of the current.

00:21:32.166 --> 00:21:32.792
Listen.

00:21:34.377 --> 00:21:35.920
Take this medicine to lower your fever.

00:21:37.005 --> 00:21:38.548
We have no time to rest anymore.

00:21:38.923 --> 00:21:40.425
We're going as soon as it gets dark.

00:22:02.905 --> 00:22:05.033
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.703
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:09.912 --> 00:22:12.707
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.832 --> 00:22:15.710
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.420 --> 00:22:18.963
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.088 --> 00:22:20.214
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.340 --> 00:22:23.426
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.677 --> 00:22:27.555
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.680 --> 00:22:30.933
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.225 --> 00:22:34.562
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:34.979 --> 00:22:37.857
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.608 --> 00:22:41.611
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.487 --> 00:22:44.322
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:09.639 --> 00:23:13.393
To wield a sword is the proof of life...

00:23:14.102 --> 00:23:16.729
Dreams are spun and desire piles up.

00:23:17.021 --> 00:23:19.399
But something pure is being lost.

00:23:20.608 --> 00:23:22.902
One who wields a sword for another.

00:23:23.277 --> 00:23:25.780
One who wields a
sword only for one's self.

00:23:26.280 --> 00:23:28.241
In the end, what awaits them?

00:23:28.616 --> 00:23:30.910
In the end, is there such thing as joy?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
Prepared for Death

00:23:37.305 --> 00:24:37.292
